{
  "text": "For the first rhTSH evaluation, patients were given rhTSH, 0.9 mg im on 2 consecutive days followed by 4 mCi 131 I 24 h later and serum Tg measurement and DxWBS on the fifth day (72 h after the last rhTSH injection) as previously described [CITATION_1] . Time from initial surgery to the first (enrollment) rhTSH test was 10 months to 35 yr (median 3.3 yr, mean 6.9 \u03ee 0.4 SEM yr). Average patient age at the time of enrollment was 44.0 \u03ee 1.3 yr and ranged from 14.4 to 88.2 (median 43.2) yr.",
